                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/151</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-12T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 12, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4446. Your 3402, June 8, 4 p. m. Lord <persName corresp="#p_CEARV1">Robert
                        Cecil</persName>, speaking for <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward
                        Grey</persName>, informs me that the passengers taken from the <hi
                        rend="italic">China</hi> are in Australia and that immediately on my
                    presentation of the matter on June 9, he asked the Admiralty what arrangements
                    had been made for their release and transportation. He seemed surprised, as I
                    was, that they had not already been released. To-day he expresses the hope of a
                    very early answer from the Admiralty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
